  }, {
    "tStartMs": 601920,
    "dDurationMs": 4160,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "interactions that we want to enable. And to make \nthis a bit more understandable, here's a really  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 606080,
    "dDurationMs": 7840,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "an example I want to give you um that showcases \nthis problem. So how can you build an MCP server  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 613920,
    "dDurationMs": 5840,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "for example that summarizes a discussion from an \nissue tracker? So on one hand side I can build  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 619760,
    "dDurationMs": 6560,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "an MCP server that exposes this kind of data very \nsimple and that's quite clear but how do I do the  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 626320,
    "dDurationMs": 8160,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "summarization step because for the summarization \nstep I obviously need a model and so there in one  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 634480,
    "dDurationMs": 6160,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "way to go and build this is you can build an \nMCP server that is this issue tracker server  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 640640,
    "dDurationMs": 7120,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "and you have a choice here you can bring your own \nSDK and call the model have the model summarizes  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 648400,
    "dDurationMs": 5120,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "But then there's a little problem to that and the \nproblem is that the client has a model selected  "
