  }, {
    "tStartMs": 662640,
    "dDurationMs": 6000,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "model the client has configured and so you bring \nyour own SDK like of of a model provider and be  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 668640,
    "dDurationMs": 5680,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "it the anthropic SDK you still need then like \na API key that this user needs to provide and  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 674320,
    "dDurationMs": 8320,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "gets very quickly very awkward and so MCP has \na little hidden feature or a little primitive  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 682640,
    "dDurationMs": 7280,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "called sampling that allows a server to request \na completion from the client. What does this  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 689920,
    "dDurationMs": 7760,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "mean? It means that the server can use a model \nindependently from like don't having to provide an  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 697680,
    "dDurationMs": 8720,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "SDK itself but in but asks the client which model \nyou have configured and the client is the one  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 706400,
    "dDurationMs": 6480,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "providing the completion to the server. And what \ndoes this do? It does two things. First of all,  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 712880,
    "dDurationMs": 6000,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "it allows the client to get full control over \nthe security, privacy and the cost. So instead of  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 718880,
    "dDurationMs": 4400,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "having to provide an additional API key, you might \ntap into the subscription that your client might  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 723280,
    "dDurationMs": 14240,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "already have. But it allows also um a second part \nwhich is that if you take multiple um if you chain  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 737520,
    "dDurationMs": 9040,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "MCP servers in an interesting way, it makes this \nwhole pattern very recursive. And what do I mean  "
    } ]
  }, {
