    "tStartMs": 1124160,
    "dDurationMs": 7840,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "application. And it really enables MCP authors to \nbind the capability of the MCP servers to a user,  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1132000,
    "dDurationMs": 6240,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "an online account, something like that. And in \norder to do that, the way this currently has to  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1138240,
    "dDurationMs": 8080,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "work in MCP is that you do this by providing \nOOTH as the authorization layer. And the MCP  "
